mises that the fairy tales rearticulate derive their force and coherence from the priority that Perrault's characters, faithful to the dominant values of the century, accord to visual representation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 7aPOETRY / European / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476479740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804764797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804764797/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles